courses.learning_outcomes:
By the end of this course, student should:
- Have a strong understanding of the necessary components for producing research;
- Be familiar with how their own research interests fit into the larger multi-disciplinary field of Chinese Studies;
- Be able to effectively use important sources and tools for advanced research on China.

By the end of this course, student should:
- Have an understanding of the key issues that characterize the evolution of Chinese law during its imperial history;
- Have a strong awareness of the range of disciplinary approaches in the study of Chinese legal culture;
- Be able to critically analyze primary documents in China’s legal history.
